
[1]severalty

   SEV'ERALTY, n. A state of separation from the rest, or from all others.
   An estate in severalty, is that which the tenant holds in his own
   right, without being joined in interest with any other person. It is
   distinguished from joint-tenacy, coparcenary and common.
